---
block_id: 027
name: hub-sdwan-zone
display_name: "Hub SD-WAN Zone Configuration"
version: 1.0.0
category: core
device_role: hub
vendor: fortinet
platform: fortigate
min_fortios: "7.4.0"

description: |
  SD-WAN zone configuration for hub. Creates SDWAN_OVERLAY zone and binds
  IPsec tunnel interfaces as members. Hub uses advpn-select to allow
  spoke-to-spoke shortcuts.

depends_on:
  - block_id: 023
    reason: "IPsec phase1 templates must exist"
  - block_id: 024
    reason: "IPsec phase2 templates must exist"

provides:
  - hub-sdwan-zone
  - hub-sdwan-overlay

parameters:
  - name: ZONE_NAME
    description: "SD-WAN zone name"
    type: string
    required: false
    default: "SDWAN_OVERLAY"

  - name: MEMBER_SEQ_VPN1
    description: "SD-WAN member sequence number for VPN1"
    type: integer
    required: false
    default: 100
    note: "Hub typically uses high seq numbers (100+)"

  - name: MEMBER_SEQ_VPN2
    description: "SD-WAN member sequence number for VPN2"
    type: integer
    required: false
    default: 2

verification:
  commands:
    - "get system sdwan"
  expected_patterns:
    - "status: enable"
    - "zone: {{ZONE_NAME}}"
    - "advpn-select: enable"

rollback:
  commands:
    - "config system sdwan"
    - "set status disable"
    - "end"

notes: |
  - advpn-select enables spoke-to-spoke shortcuts
  - Hub members use tunnel interfaces (SPOKE_VPN1, SPOKE_VPN2)
  - IMPORTANT: Hub member seq (100/2) is INDEPENDENT from spoke member seq
  - Spokes use seq 3/4 per GAP-51, hub uses 100/2 - no conflict
  - Zone is used in firewall policies instead of direct interfaces
  - GPOT clarification: Hub seq ≠ spoke seq by design

---

config system sdwan
    set status enable
    config zone
        edit "{{ZONE_NAME}}"
            set advpn-select enable
        next
    end
    config members
        edit {{MEMBER_SEQ_VPN1}}
            set interface "SPOKE_VPN1"
            set zone "{{ZONE_NAME}}"
        next
        edit {{MEMBER_SEQ_VPN2}}
            set interface "SPOKE_VPN2"
            set zone "{{ZONE_NAME}}"
        next
    end
end
